physical changes that we all

00:01:42.070 --> 00:01:46.480 align:middle line:84%
will face eventually, especially
people of my generation, Baby

00:01:46.480 --> 00:01:48.700 align:middle line:84%
Boomers, who are
really just entering

00:01:48.700 --> 00:01:53.160 align:middle line:90%
into the phase of aging.

00:01:53.160 --> 00:01:53.960 align:middle line:90%
right now.

00:01:53.960 --> 00:01:57.340 align:middle line:84%
And you were talking
about how it affects

00:01:57.340 --> 00:01:59.740 align:middle line:84%
your identity, your
sense of who you are,

00:01:59.740 --> 00:02:02.920 align:middle line:84%
and your memory of
who you've been.

00:02:02.920 --> 00:02:10.820 align:middle line:10%
>> Well, before the
stroke I played golf,

00:02:10.820 --> 00:02:20.470 align:middle line:10%
I played the cello, I drove my
sports cars with stick shift,

00:02:20.470 --> 00:02:24.790 align:middle line:10%
