00:02:24.790 --> 00:02:26.480 align:middle line:10%
>> That arm is pretty limp.

00:02:26.480 --> 00:02:27.670 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:02:27.670 --> 00:02:36.570 align:middle line:84%
And I found that I'm
suffering more if I try to--

00:02:36.570 --> 00:02:42.880 align:middle line:84%
like if I remember myself
as a golfer or a cellist.

00:02:42.880 --> 00:02:48.850 align:middle line:90%
But if I like--

00:02:48.850 --> 00:02:54.100 align:middle line:90%
the stroke is a new incarnation.

00:02:54.100 --> 00:02:55.060 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:02:55.060 --> 00:03:01.525 align:middle line:84%
>> And in this one,
I've never played golf.

00:03:01.525 --> 00:03:06.190 align:middle line:90%


00:03:06.190 --> 00:03:14.620 align:middle line:84%
And the comparison
of the past with the

00:03:14.620 --> 00:03:19.800 align:middle line:90%
now is cause for suffering.

00:03:19.800 --> 00:03:21.440 align:middle line:84%
>> It could be a
source of great pain.

00:03:21.440 --> 00:03:22.900 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:03:22.900 --> 00:03:30.142 align:middle line:84%
And now I'm no longer a golfer,
I'm a person with stroke.

00:03:30.142 --> 00:03:31.870 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:03:31.870 --> 00:03:38.470 align:middle line:84%
>> And the stroke, it opened
up whole new realms for me.

00:03:38.470 --> 00:03:47.610 align:middle line:90%
I learned quietness.

00:03:47.610 --> 00:03:55.765 align:middle line:90%
I learned respect for my body.

00:03:55.765 --> 00:04:00.530 align:middle line:90%


00:04:00.530 --> 00:04:11.040 align:middle line:84%
I learned-- see,
that's it, that like--

00:04:11.040 --> 00:04:13.270 align:middle line:90%
that quietness.

00:04:13.270 --> 00:04:16.470 align:middle line:84%
>> Because you were a teacher
of meditation for many years,

00:04:16.470 --> 00:04:18.890 align:middle line:84%
so this is a new
kind of quietness.

00:04:18.890 --> 00:04:22.990 align:middle line:84%
>> It's a forced
quietness by my brain.

00:04:22.990 --> 00:04:24.460 align:middle line:90%
>> Mm-hmm.

00:04:24.460 --> 00:04:36.590 align:middle line:90%
>> And I'm just quiet--

00:04:36.590 --> 00:04:51.650 align:middle line:84%
the-- the time my brain
stops, then I get quiet.

00:04:51.650 --> 00:04:53.083 align:middle line:90%
>> Mm-hmm.

00:04:53.083 --> 00:04:55.500 align:middle line:84%
At one point you wrote that
there's-- it's as if there's a

00:04:55.500 --> 00:04:58.770 align:middle line:84%
room in your mind where
the concepts put on clothes

00:04:58.770 --> 00:05:00.750 align:middle line:90%
and the clothes are like words.

00:05:00.750 --> 00:05:03.450 align:middle line:90%
That room is no longer there.

00:05:03.450 --> 00:05:10.590 align:middle line:84%
>> It bombed out, but
you-- it's interesting,

00:05:10.590 --> 00:05:18.190 align:middle line:84%
because the concepts are
there, but there are no words

00:05:18.190 --> 00:05:20.640 align:middle line:90%
to clothe the concepts.

00:05:20.640 --> 00:05:23.870 align:middle line:90%


00:05:23.870 --> 00:05:26.300 align:middle line:84%
>> You're getting at I
think something crucial,

00:05:26.300 --> 00:05:29.210 align:middle line:84%
that it faces people
as they become older,

00:05:29.210 --> 00:05:33.110 align:middle line:84%
as they become decrepit--
maybe a sense of uselessness.

00:05:33.110 --> 00:05:36.980 align:middle line:84%
That the world seems to value
so much if you can be active,

00:05:36.980 --> 00:05:38.090 align:middle line:90%
if you can speak.

00:05:38.090 --> 00:05:39.230 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:05:39.230 --> 00:05:41.750 align:middle line:90%
If you're young.

00:05:41.750 --> 00:05:45.020 align:middle line:84%
That's what-- it's not the
world, it's this culture.

00:05:45.020 --> 00:05:46.400 align:middle line:90%
>> Hmm.

00:05:46.400 --> 00:05:47.780 align:middle line:10%
>> Because like--

00:05:47.780 --> 00:05:50.330 align:middle line:90%


00:05:50.330 --> 00:06:00.410 align:middle line:10%
I was in a small village
that I visit in India,

00:06:00.410 --> 00:06:09.230 align:middle line:10%
and somebody said to me,
you're looking much older.

00:06:09.230 --> 00:06:13.412 align:middle line:10%
In this culture that
would be fighting words.

00:06:13.412 --> 00:06:14.245 align:middle line:10%
>> What do you mean?

00:06:14.245 --> 00:06:16.700 align:middle line:10%
>> Yeah, what do you-- yeah.

00:06:16.700 --> 00:06:19.380 align:middle line:10%
I should have gotten a suntan
or something like that.

00:06:19.380 --> 00:06:22.250 align:middle line:10%


00:06:22.250 --> 00:06:29.420 align:middle line:10%
But the way he said it, he
was like complimenting me.

00:06:29.420 --> 00:06:45.200 align:middle line:84%
Like, you're a wisdom carrier,
you are somebody we can trust.

00:06:45.200 --> 00:06:46.000 align:middle line:90%
>> An elder.

00:06:46.000 --> 00:06:46.910 align:middle line:90%
>> An elder.

00:06:46.910 --> 00:06:47.710 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:06:47.710 --> 00:06:50.260 align:middle line:84%
We don't have in our culture
the same respect for elders.

00:06:50.260 --> 00:06:51.110 align:middle line:90%
>> No, no.

00:06:51.110 --> 00:06:53.620 align:middle line:90%
No, no.

00:06:53.620 --> 00:06:56.710 align:middle line:84%
>> That's why I'm so grateful
to be able to be with you now

00:06:56.710 --> 00:07:00.280 align:middle line:84%
as you are on television because
it happens so rarely, I think.

00:07:00.280 --> 00:07:08.870 align:middle line:90%


00:07:08.870 --> 00:07:12.155 align:middle line:84%
>> Television has
very few elders.

00:07:12.155 --> 00:07:15.130 align:middle line:90%


00:07:15.130 --> 00:07:15.930 align:middle line:90%
>> I know.

00:07:15.930 --> 00:07:25.060 align:middle line:84%
>> And they have few in
advertising and few in the rest

00:07:25.060 --> 00:07:26.105 align:middle line:90%
of the programming.

00:07:26.105 --> 00:07:26.905 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:07:26.905 --> 00:07:27.705 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:07:27.705 --> 00:07:30.070 align:middle line:84%
>> And certainly very few
interviews with people who

00:07:30.070 --> 00:07:32.010 align:middle line:90%
experience aphasia.

00:07:32.010 --> 00:07:33.312 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:07:33.312 --> 00:07:37.420 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:07:37.420 --> 00:07:38.910 align:middle line:90%
>> I had a funny experience.

00:07:38.910 --> 00:07:49.130 align:middle line:90%
I was-- the hospital I was--

00:07:49.130 --> 00:07:58.850 align:middle line:84%
one of the three hospitals,
they had a conference about me,

00:07:58.850 --> 00:08:03.050 align:middle line:84%
and they were kind
enough to let me sit in.

00:08:03.050 --> 00:08:13.170 align:middle line:84%
And they were discussing
me as if I were my brain.

00:08:13.170 --> 00:08:13.970 align:middle line:90%
>> Hmm.

00:08:13.970 --> 00:08:15.320 align:middle line:90%
Or the stroke.

00:08:15.320 --> 00:08:17.210 align:middle line:90%
>> As the stroke, yes.

00:08:17.210 --> 00:08:24.770 align:middle line:84%
